1
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,767
You know Red?

2
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:21,133
Red, I love you so much.
Please don't do this.

3
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:23,767
Yes.

4
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,367
I know Red so well.

5
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:27,333
Yen!

6
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:28,767
Put your hands up!

7
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:30,167
Who are you?

8
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,367
How did you know Yenyen?

9
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:32,733
Red?
Is that you?

10
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,700
You know me?

11
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:37,433
You're the most handsome
soccer player!

12
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,067
I will look for him
around the island.

13
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,867
I'll go with you.

14
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,500
No, no. Just stay here.

15
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,600
I'll be right back
once I find him.

16
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,833
Amanda and I had a fight. Okay?

17
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:49,867
She fainted, so we left
her there.

18
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:51,500
You left her there unconscious?

19
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:52,600
Where?

20
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:54,533
I need to do something.

21
00:00:55,467 --> 00:00:56,733
I need to find Red.

22
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,500
I hope he's okay.

23
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:00,867
Red?
Oh my God!

24
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:02,267
Is that really you?

25
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:03,433
You're alive!

26
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,767
Are you okay?
Were you hurt?

27
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:06,733
Oh my God!

28
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:13,533
Red?

29
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,033
Sabina?

30
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,067
You know each other?

31
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:31,933
Yenyen!

32
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,667
Yenyen!

33
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:40,267
Yen.

34
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,733
Aren't you happy to see me?

35
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:46,867
I think I came at
the wrong time.

36
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,433
I might have interrupted you.

37
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:56,000
He's my boyfriend.

38
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:59,833
The one I told you
I was looking for.

39
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:03,833
Why?

40
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:13,433
I just did what I thought
was right, Amanda.

41
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,300
I didn't do this for you
to think I care for you.

42
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:20,400
I only helped you

43
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:22,267
because I didn't want the
situation to get worse.

44
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:25,733
I still can't forget
what you did to my son.

45
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:32,633
You should have let her
rot in that body bag

46
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:33,700
along with the dead bodies!

47
00:02:33,767 --> 00:02:35,200
She has a complete entourage.

48
00:02:35,267 --> 00:02:37,867
People without souls!

49
00:02:38,467 --> 00:02:42,333
And don't you touch
my husband again!

50
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,467
You're the heartless one!

51
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:46,500
Because you wanted to kill me.
You're a murderer!

52
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,867
You're calling me a murderer?

53
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:51,733
Hey! Why don't you look at
yourself in the mirror?

54
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,600
You are the murderer.

55
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:57,700
Your hands are still tainted
with the blood of my son!

56
00:02:58,233 --> 00:03:02,900
You're brave because you have
the money and connection.

57
00:03:02,967 --> 00:03:07,167
But I won't let slide
what you did to me!

58
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:09,600
I will sue you!

59
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:16,333
So you mean he's also the
man you're talking about?

60
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,933
The man you were with
on the other island?

61
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,633
Wow, small world, right?

62
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:25,700
Who would have
thought that we...

63
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:29,033
were talking about the same man?

64
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,900
But I'm so happy
you're finally here.

65
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:34,567
And we're together now.

66
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:37,733
Thank you, Yenyen, for
taking care of him.

67
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:41,667
Okay, I don't want
to interrupt you.

68
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:46,233
Just continue catching
up with each other.

69
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:48,733
Yen, wait!

70
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,767
Wait, where are you going, Red?

71
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,467
I'm still dizzy.
My head still hurts.

72
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:54,367
Please don't leave.

73
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,633
Don't leave me, please.

74
00:04:04,567 --> 00:04:05,133
Red!

75
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:06,833
Red, don't leave me!

76
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,467
You're so funny!

77
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:12,800
Go ahead, sue us!

78
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:15,933
You think I'm scared
of your threats?

79
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,600
Go ahead, file a case!

80
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:19,100
Rina, that's enough.

81
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:21,967
Why?

82
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,833
Do you have proof?

83
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:28,067
Do you think someone will
believe an ex-convict like you?

84
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:29,067
I may be an ex-con,

85
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:30,500
but I still have my rights.

86
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:32,633
Fine.

87
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,967
I won't take your rights.

88
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:37,567
But do you think you
can afford to sue me?

89
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:41,233
You don't even have
transportation money to go

90
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:43,433
from the slums you live
to the court!

91
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,367
And now you're telling me
you're gonna file a case?

92
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:47,267
Not everything can be
bought with money.

93
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:48,167
Oh, Amanda!

94
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:49,633
That's where you're wrong!

95
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:53,267
If you have don't money,
you have nothing!

96
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:56,867
And I just have a piece
of advice for you, Amanda.

97
00:04:56,933 --> 00:05:00,500
If you have money left in
your piggy bank,

98
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,400
I suggest you keep it
for buying food.

99
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:04,667
So you won't be delusional.

100
00:05:04,733 --> 00:05:10,733
You need all your strength
to prove that you have rights.

101
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:14,467
Because that's all you
have for now, at least.

102
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:19,667
I will do everything to
file a case against you.

103
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:20,267
Oh, well.

104
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,967
Then I'll see you in court.

105
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,100
Let's go, Victor.

106
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:26,733
Let's go.

107
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:39,967
Yen, wait!

108
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:41,600
Wait, let me explain!

109
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:42,767
Yen!

110
00:05:43,867 --> 00:05:45,433
Everything you saw earlier...

111
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,333
I didn't know why it happened.
She kissed me.

112
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,300
I saw it!

113
00:05:50,867 --> 00:05:52,133
I'm not dumb!

114
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,567
I get that your
girlfriend kissed you.

115
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:56,733
- Because she missed you!
- She's not my girlfriend!

116
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,633
So what's that?!
A fling?!

117
00:05:59,533 --> 00:06:01,133
What's that, Red?
Just a fling?

118
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,433
No feelings involved?

119
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:06,567
You kiss anyone even if
you don't have feelings?

120
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,567
So what's that?

121
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,167
So what about us?

122
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:16,000
Was it just a game, Red?

123
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:25,733
Well, you know, you really
are a good player.

124
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:29,933
Both literally and figuratively.

125
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,267
I didn't...

126
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,600
- hear me out first.
- No!

127
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:36,867
- Stop it!
- Listen to me!

128
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:38,933
- I didn't toy with you.
- Don't touch me!

129
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,633
I didn't toy with you, okay?

130
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,833
Everything that happened
to us was real!

131
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:50,767
Okay, I'm sorry I
didn't tell you.

132
00:06:51,367 --> 00:06:53,233
I didn't tell you about Sab.

133
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,067
Because she doesn't
matter to me.

134
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,900
Yes, she's my ex-girlfriend!

135
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:03,100
- Ex-girlfriend!
- If she's your ex,

136
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:06,600
why did she react that way
when she saw you?

137
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:08,033
She wouldn't act that way

138
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,467
- if you two were over!
- Yenyen!

139
00:07:09,533 --> 00:07:11,233
- I'm telling the truth!
- She wouldn't act that way

140
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,400
if you were over!

141
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:14,500
- I'm telling the truth!
- Stay away from me, Red!

142
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,400
Please, believe me!

143
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:17,333
Believe me, please!

144
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,033
Please, Yenyen, I'm
telling the truth.

145
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,500
Please, believe me.

146
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:24,233
I don't know why she's
acting that way.

147
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,933
You're a liar.

148
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,967
- You're a liar!
- I don't know why she's...

149
00:07:28,033 --> 00:07:29,267
You're a liar, Red!

150
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,700
Liar!

151
00:07:32,767 --> 00:07:33,267
Yen.

152
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,367
Yen, Yen.

153
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:39,267
- Leave me out of your mess!
- Yen, listen to me...

154
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,300
Leave me out of your mess!

155
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,333
- Stop it, Red!
- We made a promise, right?

156
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,033
We promised each other.

157
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:52,100
We'll never leave each other.

158
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:54,867
Yenyen, I know...

159
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,900
what we both have is real.

160
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:58,767
Why...

161
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:01,133
why are you throwing it away?

162
00:08:04,133 --> 00:08:05,033
Sorry!

163
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:08,733
Sorry because I didn't
mean to fall for you!

164
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:11,233
I didn't mean it.

165
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,233
Why can't you believe

166
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,467
- what I'm saying, Yen?
- I don't know!

167
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:19,233
But I know someone's
between us!

168
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:21,767
If you two are over,
why does she still

169
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:23,667
- clings to you, Red?
- I don't know!

170
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:25,667
- Why is she clinging to you?
- I don't know!

171
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,967
Because she hasn't
moved on from me yet!

172
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,333
- Liar!
- She hasn't moved on

173
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,433
from me yet, Yen!

174
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,867
That's the truth!

175
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:35,567
I don't know!
Don't blame me!

176
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,533
Don't blame me.

177
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,167
No.

178
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:47,233
- I want to stay out of it.
- Believe me!

179
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,267
Red, I don't want anything

180
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:49,800
- to do with your situation.
- Believe me.

181
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:50,700
I want to stay out of it!

182
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,100
Leave me alone.

183
00:08:55,267 --> 00:08:56,533
- Yen, please.
- I didn't survive

184
00:08:56,600 --> 00:09:00,167
the plane crash and be on this
island only worry about that!

185
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:02,867
I want to survive.

186
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,700
I want to go back to my mother.

187
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,300
- Yen, please.
- Leave me alone!

188
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:09,367
You're a liar!

189
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:11,167
Yen, please.

190
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:27,700
What the hell was that, Rina?

191
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:30,167
Why did you do that to Amanda?

192
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,267
What do you want to do?
Kill her?

193
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:44,200
If that's what I should do
to have peace of mind...

194
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:48,667
so be it.

195
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,667
Do you hear yourself?

196
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:54,667
If you do that...

197
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:57,733
what makes you different
from her?

198
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,600
And now, she's planning
to file charges.

199
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:04,067
You can go to jail
for what you did.

200
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:05,400
Fine.

201
00:10:06,667 --> 00:10:08,567
She can sue me.

202
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:10,367
I'm not afraid of her.

203
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:14,300
Don't forget, Victor.

204
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:16,933
We're the victims here.

205
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:21,700
We lost our son because
of that wench.

206
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:26,800
But it seems that
you're siding with her.

207
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:30,233
Like everything doesn't
matter to you.

208
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:33,600
I'm not taking her side.

209
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:37,433
I just don't want our family
to get ruined again.

210
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,167
And I don't want my name...

211
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,667
and reputation in the banking
community ruined

212
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,100
because of your foolishness.

213
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,967
So what do you want me to do?

214
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,933
Forget everything?

215
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,533
That's not easy for me.

216
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:13,267
Rina, listen.

217
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:17,833
No matter what you do to Amanda,

218
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:21,900
you can't bring Angelo
back to life.

219
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:24,700
We have two sons.

220
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:29,033
It's not just Angelo.
We still have Red.

221
00:11:30,633 --> 00:11:34,600
Why don't you focus your
efforts on finding Red?

222
00:11:51,633 --> 00:11:52,900
Raichu?

223
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:53,900
Eden?

224
00:11:53,967 --> 00:11:55,167
Raichu!

225
00:11:55,233 --> 00:11:56,333
Eden!

226
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,433
Eden!

227
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:59,700
Eden!

228
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:01,800
It's really you!

229
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:03,000
Eden, Eden!

230
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:04,567
Is it really you?

231
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:06,300
Oh my, it's really you!

232
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:08,467
- Eden!
- Raichu!

233
00:12:12,467 --> 00:12:13,933
Raichu, you're alive!

234
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:18,633
You don't know how happy I am
to see you here, Raichu!

235
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,033
Eden!

236
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,033
- Raichu!
- I thought I wouldn't

237
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,467
see you again, Eden.

238
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,733
I'm so happy to see you.

239
00:12:30,033 --> 00:12:32,100
- Raichu.
- You know, I even accepted

240
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:36,000
that I would end up with Tarzan
in this jungle life.

241
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:38,200
Raichu, you know what...

242
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,633
I wish Coach was with us.

243
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:46,700
I heard about it.

244
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:51,033
But Eden...

245
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:55,233
it's hard for me to accept
what happened to her.

246
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:59,367
But you're still lucky you
got the chance

247
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:01,867
to be with her in her
last moments.

248
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:07,933
Let's just think that Coach
is happy wherever she is.

249
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,333
Because we're now together.

250
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:15,300
And we should never
give up, right?

251
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:19,033
See, we got reunited.

252
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:23,200
Who would have thought
that we'd survived?

253
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:24,900
Right?

254
00:13:26,233 --> 00:13:29,967
Raichu, there's a reason
why we're alive.

255
00:13:32,167 --> 00:13:32,967
Right?

256
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:39,567
Raichu...

257
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:43,333
do you know there's
another survivor?

258
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,400
She's also from our school.

259
00:13:46,467 --> 00:13:47,633
Did you see her?

260
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,167
I know you'll come back.

261
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:55,833
Why did you tell Yenyen
I'm your boyfriend?

262
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,867
Because it's the truth.

263
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:00,933
What?

264
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:03,467
Did I miss anything?

265
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,200
Did you get amnesia
from the plane crash?

266
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,467
Sab, we broke up before
we left Davao!

267
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:12,233
Why? Did I say yes to it?

268
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,233
A breakup is a mutual
decision, Red.

269
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:18,133
I disagree with it, which
means we're not over yet.

270
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:23,367
And why are you getting mad?

271
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:25,200
I should get mad at you instead.

272
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:29,533
You think I don't know what you
were doing on the other island?

273
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:32,133
Yenyen told me everything!

274
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:34,633
You were flirting with her

275
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:37,667
instead of thinking of ways
how to fix our relationship!

276
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:44,967
Eden, I didn't know because
I hid in the cave.

277
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:50,033
I get supplies by the beach
and then go back there.

278
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:53,533
You're lucky you
were with someone.

279
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:54,400
And it's Red.

280
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,933
I wish I didn't meet Red.

281
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,133
What?

282
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:03,567
Come on, Eden!

283
00:15:04,133 --> 00:15:06,900
Of all people,

284
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:11,700
you ended up being with the most
good-looking and hottest man!

285
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:14,700
OMG!

286
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:22,100
Eden, for all the days
you were together,

287
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,667
don't tell me you didn't
fall for each other.

288
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:29,933
We can't, Raichu.

289
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:33,200
Someone will get hurt.

290
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,267
Come here.

291
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:38,500
I missed you.

292
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:40,567
Eden, come on.
I won't get hurt.

293
00:15:40,633 --> 00:15:43,033
Red and I are over, okay?

294
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:44,900
It's okay.

295
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:47,133
Raichu, I missed you!

296
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:50,300
First of all, I wasn't
flirting around.

297
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,400
Secondly, I'd rather
think of surviving

298
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:55,600
instead of things that
are already over.

299
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:57,033
And that's us!

300
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,733
- We're over!
- No.

301
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:01,133
I can't accept that.

302
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,700
Please, we're not over yet.
Please, Red.

303
00:16:03,767 --> 00:16:05,900
Please, give me another chance.
Don't leave me.

304
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,333
I'm begging you.

305
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,633
I need you now more than ever.

306
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:10,300
It's like...

307
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:14,067
I will do everything, anything,
just to win you back again.

308
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:15,233
Just to make you mine again.

309
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:17,633
Please, don't leave me.
Not this time.

310
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:21,267
Please.

311
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:56,500
Sabina, thank you for the food.

312
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,400
You gave us food too.

313
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,267
Hi, Sabina!

314
00:17:02,633 --> 00:17:04,733
I'm Raichu.
It's me.

315
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,367
Don't worry.

316
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:09,467
We're not staying long.

317
00:17:10,767 --> 00:17:13,200
We'll sleep in Raichu's shelter.

318
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,100
We don't want to disturb you.

319
00:17:16,033 --> 00:17:17,233
Do as you wish.

320
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:21,000
You don't have to
stay away from us.

321
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:22,500
I won't allow it.

322
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:24,767
It's too dangerous if
we won't stay together.

323
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:26,967
We're safer here.

324
00:17:30,333 --> 00:17:31,233
I agree.

325
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:33,433
Red is right.

326
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:36,933
It's better if we stay together.

327
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:43,967
And just a piece of advice...

328
00:17:44,033 --> 00:17:48,133
can you set aside your
feelings for now?

329
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:51,633
Because we need
to work together.

330
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,433
We need each other.

331
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:56,233
We need to survive.

332
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,367
We need to get out of here.

333
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:01,500
So if you have issues,

334
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:04,500
deal with them when
we get back to Manila.

335
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:05,333
Don't deal with it here.

336
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:07,133
Is that okay?

337
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:09,533
Is it a deal?

338
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,167
Rina's lucky I wasn't there.

339
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:38,467
I would have hit her.

340
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,967
She's too much.

341
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:45,267
I would have punched her
more than 1000 times

342
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:47,000
because of what she did!

343
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,767
You're already trying
to survive,

344
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:51,333
yet she wants to kill you.

345
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,167
She's really evil.

346
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:58,133
I don't want to see her face
anymore if it were up to me.

347
00:18:58,233 --> 00:19:01,567
I'm so tired of fighting her.

348
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:05,667
I keep seeing that woman...

349
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:10,033
even if I want to live my life

350
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:13,167
and focus my attention
on finding my daughter!

351
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:16,433
She won't stop until your dead!

352
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:19,433
Her evilness is on
another level.

353
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:20,367
Nothing compares to it.

354
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,833
That's why I want
to end all this.

355
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:30,233
I don't want Eden to worry about
my past when she returns.

356
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:36,000
I will make Rina suffer the same
way she makes me suffer.

357
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:43,267
I will sue her, Dindi.

358
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:46,267
What?

359
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,767
Can we do that?

360
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:53,000
That's the only way I could
think of to make her stop.

361
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:04,300
Yenyen?

362
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:08,300
I found some bamboo over there.

363
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:13,200
Don't worry, I'll help
you make your shelter.

364
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:16,067
So you'll have a place
to sleep tonight.

365
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:20,867
And...

366
00:20:20,933 --> 00:20:24,367
I'm sorry I didn't tell you

367
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:25,700
about my connection
with Red sooner.

368
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:30,900
I thought that wasn't
the right time

369
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,567
to tell you that
I'm his girlfriend,

370
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:35,767
especially since you were
still recovering.

371
00:20:37,033 --> 00:20:39,167
I understand, Sabina.

372
00:20:42,167 --> 00:20:43,933
But I don't understand...

373
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:50,233
why Red is telling me
that you two are over.

374
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:52,400
No.

375
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:54,200
No, that's not true.

376
00:20:54,967 --> 00:20:56,567
Red is lying.

377
00:20:57,733 --> 00:21:00,233
I don't know what his
intentions are,

378
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,800
but it's not true
that we broke up.

379
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:08,100
Actually, he's really like that.

380
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:13,300
I caught him with another
woman several times.

381
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:17,600
I caught him cheating
on me a few times.

382
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,733
But I always chose to
forgive him because...

383
00:21:24,133 --> 00:21:25,933
I just love him so much.

384
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,200
So I'm begging you.

385
00:21:33,733 --> 00:21:37,133
Stay away from Red.

386
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,300
Stay away from him.

387
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,033
Because I know him.

388
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,000
He's lost.

389
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:48,533
He doesn't know what he's doing.

390
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:52,833
Maybe he's confused.

391
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,733
And no one can understand him...

392
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,167
but me.

393
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,300
I need him...

394
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,467
in ways that he needs me too.

395
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,267
So I'm asking you,

396
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,533
as a fellow woman...

397
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,400
just please stay away
from my boyfriend.

398
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,667
Because I just can't afford
to lose him again.

399
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:55,267
Yen.

400
00:22:57,833 --> 00:23:00,367
Raichu told me you wanted
to talk to me.

401
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:04,400
I knew you would
realize everything.

402
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:07,700
I know that you believe me.

403
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:18,800
From now on...

404
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:23,033
let's forget everything that
happened on the island.

405
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:28,067
Let's end whatever relationship
we have...

406
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:33,900
for your girlfriend's sake.

407
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:40,367
I won't accept that.

408
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,933
Sabina and I are over.

409
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,600
For you, yes.

410
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:50,633
But for Sabina, you
two aren't over yet.

411
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:54,200
Red, she loves you so much.

412
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:58,367
I don't want to hurt
someone else.

413
00:24:01,133 --> 00:24:03,433
I don't want to be
like my mom,

414
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:07,833
who got hurt when
my father left us.

415
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:08,367
Yen...

416
00:24:09,433 --> 00:24:14,467
Red, we both know that we'll
return to our own lives

417
00:24:14,533 --> 00:24:16,233
when we return to Manila, right?

418
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:20,833
I'll go back to my mom.

419
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:24,933
And you'll go back
to your parents...

420
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:26,833
to Sabina.

421
00:24:30,667 --> 00:24:32,767
So you should work things out.

422
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,767
Stay away from me, Red.

423
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:40,767
Yen.
Wait.

424
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:02,033
I want to have
my direction back.

425
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:07,433
And that's to reunite
with my mother.

426
00:25:08,467 --> 00:25:11,500
I want to be with
my mom again.

427
00:25:11,933 --> 00:25:15,100
Don't you appreciate
everything I do for you?

428
00:25:15,633 --> 00:25:17,567
I know that I have a lot of
shortcomings

429
00:25:17,633 --> 00:25:18,800
in our relationship.

430
00:25:18,867 --> 00:25:22,767
But please, just give our
relationship a second chance.

431
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:25,367
If she has the intent
to kill you,

432
00:25:25,433 --> 00:25:27,367
that's frustrated homicide.

433
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:31,833
And I'll be honest with you,
it's not going to be easy.

434
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,200
Are you ready financially
for this?

435
00:25:34,267 --> 00:25:35,567
Do we have to pay for it?

436
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:40,700
Next time, think before
you make a mess.

437
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:47,533
I won't make a mess anymore once
I finish cleaning the trash.

438
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:49,033
Come on.

439
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:50,333
Let's catch some fish.

440
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:51,600
Hey!

441
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:54,633
Wow, fabulous!

442
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:56,600
Candidate number two
is so ready

443
00:25:56,667 --> 00:25:58,900
for the swimming competition.

444
00:25:58,967 --> 00:25:59,700
Judge!

445
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:03,067
What can you say about
her performance?
